# Welcome

This comprehensive guide explores the fascinating world of Physical AI and Humanoid Robotics, covering everything from fundamental concepts to advanced implementation techniques.

Physical AI represents the convergence of artificial intelligence with physical robotics, enabling machines to perceive, learn, and interact with the real world in increasingly sophisticated ways. This textbook provides a structured approach to understanding and building intelligent robotic systems.

## About

This textbook is designed for students, researchers, and practitioners who want to:

- Understand the fundamentals of physical AI and humanoid robotics
- Learn practical implementation techniques using modern frameworks
- Explore real-world applications and case studies
- Build hands-on projects with cutting-edge technologies

Content coming soon.

## Getting Started

To get the most out of this textbook, you should have:

- Basic programming knowledge (Python, C++, or similar)
- Understanding of fundamental mathematics (linear algebra, calculus)
- Curiosity about robotics and artificial intelligence
- Access to development tools and simulation environments

Content coming soon.

## Next Steps

As you progress through this textbook, you'll explore topics including:

- Robot Operating System (ROS 2) fundamentals
- Computer vision and perception systems
- Motion planning and control
- Machine learning for robotics
- Human-robot interaction
- Advanced humanoid robot design

